The witness has detailed that at about 4:30 p.m., Locklear "was stepping deep on the accelerator, making a lot of noise, trying to get the car out of the parking lot back and forth, and going back and forth passed several times over his sunglasses".
Shortly after, the witness, who apparently had not recognized the actress at first, saw Locklear stop on a nearby highway and get out of the vehicle.
This person was the one who alerted the emergency services because "she was worried about Locklear's life".
When the police patrol arrived they found the actress sitting inside her vehicle, which was partially blocking the road.
"She looked disoriented", so the agents took her to a drug and alcohol specialist center to run a test.
According to a police spokesman, the actress was cooperative and the excessive alcohol was ruled out from the start, although "as observed by officers at first sight, we believe Locklear was under the influence of some medication".
Locklear was arrested on suspicion of driving under the influence of an unspecified substance and entered the local jail at about 7 p.m. although she was released a few hours later.
Two months ago, Locklear came out of a treatment clinic in Arizona recovering from an episode of anxiety and depression.
